          "id": "math-c-fcb4a7999f58f031",
          "title": "The points $(9, -5)$ and $(-3, -1)$ are the endpoints of a diameter of a circle. What is the sum of the coordinates of t...",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 3):**\nThe points $(9, -5)$ and $(-3, -1)$ are the endpoints of a diameter of a circle. What is the sum of the coordinates of the center of the circle?\n\n**Solution:**\nThe center of the circle is located at the midpoint of any diameter. Thus, the center of the circle is $\\left(\\frac{9+(-3)}{2}, \\frac{(-5)+(-1)}{2}\\right) = (3, -3)$. The sum of the coordinates of the center of the circle is therefore $3 + (-3) = \\boxed{0}$.",
          "kind": "example"
