          "id": "math-8b3f9433d982d03e",
          "front": "The sum of two numbers is $45$. Their difference is $3$. What is the lesser of the two numbers?",
          "back": "Let $x,y$ be the larger and smaller numbers, respectively. We have $x+y=45$ and $x-y=3$. Thus: $y=\\frac{1}{2}((x+y)-(x-y))=\\frac{1}{2}(45-3)=\\boxed{21}$.",
          "hint": "Category: Algebra, Difficulty: 1/5"
