          "id": "math-c-fc4f1a27aa984b2a",
          "title": "A geometric sequence of positive integers is formed for which the first term is 3 and the fourth term is 192. What is th...",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 2):**\nA geometric sequence of positive integers is formed for which the first term is 3 and the fourth term is 192. What is the third term of the sequence?\n\n**Solution:**\nLet the geometric sequence have common ratio $r$. We know that $3\\cdot r^3=192$, or $r=4$. Thus, the third term is $3 \\cdot r^2 = 3 \\cdot 4^2 = \\boxed{48}$.",
          "kind": "example"
