          "id": "math-0b8b2e2d829e8830",
          "front": "Sixteen is 64$\\%$ of what number?",
          "back": "If the number is $x$, we can set up the equation $\\frac{16}{x}=\\frac{64}{100}$. We divide both sides by $4$ to get $\\frac{1}{x}=\\frac{4}{100}=\\frac{1}{25}$, so $x=\\boxed{25}$.",
          "hint": "Category: Algebra, Difficulty: 1/5"
