          "id": "math-c-0a917119267d7946",
          "title": "Given the function $f(x)=3x^3+2$, find the value of $x$ so that $f^{-1}(x)=4$.",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 4):**\nGiven the function $f(x)=3x^3+2$, find the value of $x$ so that $f^{-1}(x)=4$.\n\n**Solution:**\nThe equation $f^{-1}(x)=4$ is equivalent to $x=f(4)$.  Therefore we want to find the value $f(4)$. We compute $f(4) = 3 \\cdot 4^3 + 2 = \\boxed{194}$.",
