          "title": "Find $x$ such that $\\log_x 81=\\log_2 16$.",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 2):**\nFind $x$ such that $\\log_x 81=\\log_2 16$.\n\n**Solution:**\nWe begin by evaluating (or simplifying) the RHS of the equation. Since $2^4=16$, we know that $\\log_2 16=4$, so we have $\\log_x 81=4$. Writing this equation in exponential form, we get that $x^4=81$. This gives us the possible solutions $x=\\pm3$. However since the base of a logarithm is always positive, $x$ must equal $\\boxed{3}$.",
