          "id": "math-c-498020899fe8da6d",
          "title": "Solve  \\[\\frac{x^2+x+1}{x+1}=x+2\\]for $x$.",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 3):**\nSolve  \\[\\frac{x^2+x+1}{x+1}=x+2\\]for $x$.\n\n**Solution:**\nCross-multiplication gives  \\[x^2+x+1=(x+2)(x+1)=x^2+3x+2.\\]Therefore \\[0=2x+1\\]and $x=\\boxed{-\\frac12}$.",
          "kind": "example"
