          "id": "math-ff4dd76a55df9d15",
          "front": "Max bought a new dirt bike and paid $10\\%$ of the cost upfront, which was $\\$150$. What was the price of the bike?",
          "back": "If $10\\%$ of the price of the dirt bike was $\\$150$, then $100\\%$ of the price must have been ten times the amount that Max paid upfront. Therefore, the price of the bike must have been $10 \\times \\$150=\\boxed{\\$ 1500}$.",
          "hint": "Category: Algebra, Difficulty: 1/5"
