          "back": "Since $4096=2^{12}$, one of these is an integer if the number on the root is a factor of 12. Therefore, the only numbers in the list that are integers are $\\sqrt{4096}=2^6=64$, $\\sqrt[3]{4096}=2^4=16$, $\\sqrt[4]{4096}=2^3=8$, $\\sqrt[6]{4096}=2^2=4$ and $\\sqrt[12]{4096}=2$. This makes $\\boxed{5}$ integers in all.",
