          "title": "Simplify: $x(3x^2-2)-5(x^2-2x+7)$. Express your answer in the form $Ax^3+Bx^2+Cx+D.$",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 3):**\nSimplify: $x(3x^2-2)-5(x^2-2x+7)$. Express your answer in the form $Ax^3+Bx^2+Cx+D.$\n\n**Solution:**\nUsing the distributive property and combining like terms: \\begin{align*}\nx(3x^2-2)-5(x^2-2x+7) &= 3x^3-2x-5x^2+10x-35\\\\\n& = \\boxed{3x^3-5x^2+8x-35}.\n\\end{align*}",
