          "front": "What is the absolute value of the difference between the squares of 101 and 99?",
          "back": "$101^2>99^2$, so $|101^2-99^2|=101^2-99^2$. This factors as a difference of squares into $(101-99)(101+99)=2\\cdot200=\\boxed{400}$.",
          "hint": "Category: Algebra, Difficulty: 2/5"
