          "front": "What is the positive difference of the solutions of $\\dfrac{r^2-3r-17}{r+4}=2r+7$?",
          "back": "Factoring the quadratic in the numerator does not look pleasant, so we go ahead and multiply through by the denominator to get \\begin{align*}\nr^2-3r-17&=(r+4)(2r+7)\\\\\nr^2-3r-17&=2r^2 + 15r + 28\\\\\nr^2+18r+45&=0\\\\\n(r+3)(r+15)&=0\n\\end{align*}Therefore the solutions are $r=-3$ and $r=-15$ which have a difference of $\\boxed{12}$.",
