          "title": "What is the distance on a Cartesian coordinate plane from $(1, -1)$ to  $(7, 7)?$",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 2):**\nWhat is the distance on a Cartesian coordinate plane from $(1, -1)$ to  $(7, 7)?$\n\n**Solution:**\nUsing the distance formula, we get that the distance is $$\\sqrt{ (1-7)^2 + (-1-7)^2} = \\sqrt{36+64} = \\sqrt{100} = \\boxed{10}.$$",
          "kind": "example"
