          "front": "Let \\[f(n) =\n\\begin{cases}\nn^2-1 & \\text{ if }n < 4,\n\\\\ 3n-2 & \\text{ if }n \\geq 4.\n\\end{cases}\n\\]Find $f(f(f(2)))$.",
          "back": "Working from the inside out, since $2<4$ we have that $f(2)=(2)^2-1=3$. Continuing, since $3<4$ we have that $f(f(2))=f(3)=(3)^2-1=8$. Finally, since $8 \\geq 4$ we have that $f(f(f(2)))=f(8)=3(8)-2=\\boxed{22}$.",
