          "front": "How many miles can a car travel in 20 minutes if it travels $ \\, \\frac{3}{4} \\, $ as fast as a train going 80 miles per hour?",
          "back": "The car travels at a speed of $$\\frac{3}{4}\\times80\\text{ miles per hour}=3\\times20=60\\text{ miles per hour}.$$ In $20$ minutes, the car travels $$\\frac{60 \\text{ miles}}{60\\text{ minutes}}\\times20\\text{ minutes}=1\\times20=\\boxed{20\\text{ miles}}.$$",
