          "id": "math-c-67baea7e2869d99f",
          "title": "How many integers are there in the solution set of $|x-2| \\leq 5.6$?",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 4):**\nHow many integers are there in the solution set of $|x-2| \\leq 5.6$?\n\n**Solution:**\nSince $|x-2|$ is an integer, it can equal 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, or 5.  If $|x-2| = 0$, we have only one solution for $x$.  Otherwise we have 2.  This leads to a total of $\\boxed{11}$ integers in the solution set.",
