        {
          "id": "math-c-32fb0e6bb6e06278",
          "title": "If $9s+5t=108$ and $s$ is two less than $t$, what is $t$?",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 2):**\nIf $9s+5t=108$ and $s$ is two less than $t$, what is $t$?\n\n**Solution:**\nFirst we begin by solving the system of equations \\begin{align*}\n9s+5t&=108, \\\\\nt-2&=s.\n\\end{align*}Making the substitution for $s$ from the second equation to the first, we get $9(t-2)+5t=108$, which simplifies to $14t-18=108$. Solving for $t$, we find that $t=\\frac{108+18}{14}=\\boxed{9}$.",
          "kind": "example"
        }
