          "id": "math-e74de161b1c172a1",
          "front": "Find $x$ such that $\\log_x 4=\\log_{27} 3$.",
          "back": "We begin by evaluating the RHS of the equation. Since $27=3^3$, we know that $27^{\\frac13}=3$ and $\\log_{27} 3=\\frac13$. This allows us to simplify the original equation as $\\log_x 4=\\frac13$. Writing this equation in exponential form, we get $x^{\\frac13}=4$, which gives us the solution $x=4^3=\\boxed{64}$.",
          "hint": "Category: Algebra, Difficulty: 3/5"
