          "id": "math-c-0553342748b20662",
          "title": "Factor $9y^2-30y+25$.",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 3):**\nFactor $9y^2-30y+25$.\n\n**Solution:**\nThe quadratic is the square of $3y$,  the constant term is the square of $-5$, and the linear term equals $2(3y)(-5)$, so we have $9y^2 -30y + 25 = \\boxed{(3y - 5)^2}$.",
          "kind": "example"
