          "id": "math-c-a9c888d06d5b3be8",
          "title": "If $a @ b$ is defined as $a @ b$ = $3a - 3b$, what is the value of $3 @ 5$?",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 2):**\nIf $a @ b$ is defined as $a @ b$ = $3a - 3b$, what is the value of $3 @ 5$?\n\n**Solution:**\nYou should note quickly in your head that $3a - 3b = 3(a-b)$.  Then, plugging in $a = 3$ and $b=5$, we get $3(3-5) = 3(-2) = \\boxed{-6}$.",
          "kind": "example"
