          "title": "Let \\[f(x) =\n\\begin{cases}\n2x + 9 &\\text{if }x<-2, \\\\\n5-2x&\\text{if }x\\ge -2.\n\\end{cases}\n\\]Find $f(3).$",
          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 2):**\nLet \\[f(x) =\n\\begin{cases}\n2x + 9 &\\text{if }x<-2, \\\\\n5-2x&\\text{if }x\\ge -2.\n\\end{cases}\n\\]Find $f(3).$\n\n**Solution:**\nBecause $3\\ge -2,$ we use the second case to determine that $f(3) = 5-2(3) = \\boxed{-1}.$",
