          "id": "math-df6fbd6225deae28",
          "front": "The bacteria in a jar triple every 20 seconds. After three minutes, there are 275,562 bacteria in the jar. How many were in the jar at the beginning of the experiment?",
          "back": "After three minutes, the number of bacteria $n$ has tripled $9$ times.  This gives us the equation $n \\cdot 3^9 = 275,\\!562$, or $19,\\!683n=275,\\!562$, so $n = \\boxed{14}$",
