          "front": "What is the least integer whose square is 48 more than its double?",
          "back": "From the information given, we have $x^2 = 2x + 48$. Rearranging, we get $x^2 - 2x - 48 = 0$, which we can factor as $(x+6)(x-8) = 0$. Therefore, $x = -6\\text{ or }8$.  Since we want the lesser, $\\boxed{-6}$ is our answer.",
          "hint": "Category: Algebra, Difficulty: 4/5"
