          "id": "math-207d87e791422bca",
          "front": "A freight train travels 1 mile in 1 minute 30 seconds. At this rate, how many miles will the train travel in 1 hour?",
          "back": "The train travels 1 mile in 1 minute 30 seconds. Then it will travel 2 miles in 3 minutes. Since 60 minutes contains 20 groups of 3 minutes, the train will travel $20 \\times 2 = \\boxed{40}$ miles in 1 hour.",
          "hint": "Category: Algebra, Difficulty: 1/5"
