          "content": "**Problem (Algebra, Level 2):**\nEvaluate $$64^{1/2}\\cdot27^{-1/3}\\cdot16^{1/4}.$$\n\n**Solution:**\nEvaluate the factors separately: $64^{1/2}=(8^2)^{1/2}=8$, while $27^{-1/3}=\\frac{1}{(3^3)^{1/3}}=\\frac13$, and $16^{1/4}=(2^4)^{1/4}=2$. Multiply the simplified factors together to obtain the answer of $\\boxed{\\frac{16}{3}}$.",
          "kind": "example"
